===Etymology===
Attested since 1832; either from {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|socialisme}} or from {{suffix|en|social|ism}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GA}} {{IPA|/ˈsoʊʃəlɪzəm/|lang=en}}
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ˈsəʊʃəlɪzəm/|lang=en}}
* {{hyphenation|so|cial|ism|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# Any of various economic and political theories advocating collective or governmental ownership and administration of the means of production and distribution of goods.
## A system of social and economic equality in which there is no private property.
## A system or condition of society in which the means of production are owned and controlled by the state.

